	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64714942">Back before I knew what SMR drives were I used one to replace a drive that had failed.  Shortly after went on a brought 4 more large SMR drives for a new array.  Not long after that the first SMR drive 'failed' taking the array into a degraded state.  Investigating why a new drive failed was when I learnt the expensive truth, I had brought 5 expensive paper weights.  The core problem being the SMR drives periodically stall while they do their internal bullshit to pretend they are real HDDs.  The Linux RAID</div>
	</div>

