	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64714992"><p>I got bitten by this exact same thing when I was experimenting with RAID 1 on external USB drives in the 2.5" form factor.  Found that almost all small drives are SMR.  To boot, if I tried to use them with LUKS + dm-integrity, it could take weeks to "format" the drive with all the ECC needed.  I wound up just using them as drives for offsite, GFS backups, using LUKS with btrfs using sha256 hashes for the checksumming, so there is some type of authenticated encryption present, even though btrfs's checksums w<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

