<div id="comment_64714380" class="cw">
	<div id="comment_top_64714380" class="commentTop newcomment">
		<div class="title">
			<h4><a rel="nofollow" id="comment_link_64714380" name="comment_link_64714380" href="//hardware.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23425480&amp;cid=64714380" onclick="return D2.setFocusComment(64714380)" >Why NAS?</a>


		 	<span id="comment_score_64714380" class="score"> (<a href="#" onclick="getModalPrefs('modcommentlog', 'Moderation Comment Log', 64714380); return false"><span class=opt>Score:</span>4</a>, Interesting)</span></h4>
		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a rel="nofollow" href="//slashdot.org/~Anubis+IV">Anubis IV</a>  <span class="uid"><a rel="nofollow" href="//slashdot.org/~Anubis+IV">( 1279820 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64714380">		
		on Saturday August 17, 2024 @05:44PM (<span class="ind"></span><a rel="nofollow" href="//hardware.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23425480&amp;cid=64714380">#64714380</a>)
		<small> </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64714380"><p>You can save a lot <i>if</i> you already have an always-on machine by simply using direct-attached storage (e.g. a $100-200 four-bay enclosure from Mediasonic can hold ~60TB even with a parity drive) and setting up a network share in a few minutes. You can avoid vendor lock-in or other issues, plus Backblaze will back all of it up without any gymnastics. If you don&rsquo;t have that always-on machine though, then yeah, NAS makes sense.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64714380">
<span class="ind"></span><a id="reply_link_64714380" class="btn link" href="//hardware.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23425480&amp;op=Reply&amp;threshold=1&amp;commentsort=0&amp;mode=thread&amp;pid=64714380" onclick="D2.replyTo(64714380); return false;">Reply to This</a> 	<a rel="nofollow" href="#" class="comment_share_toggle btn link">Share</a>
