			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64714900"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64714900"><p>That is a hard to beat setup.  Add a pair of SSDs as a ZIL/SLOG, and you now have incoming I/O landing at SSD speed, so some process that is doing a ton of random stuff is not going to affect writes from other items.</p><p>Backups are easy as well.  A ZFS send to an external drive, and all data is saved off securely, and one can do a GFS rotation.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64714900">

