	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64714890"><p>I started out with a Synology DS213 with a pair of 2TB WD Red drives about 13 years ago. When that ran out of room I purchased a Synology DS216 with a pair of 4TB WD Red drives. When that ran out of room I purchased a Synology DS218 with a pair of 8TB WD Red drives. All three Synology NAS boxes still run perfectly! About 6 years ago one of the 4TB drives died but it was still under warranty. I put the new drive in and after the NAS rebuilt the image was back in business. I use the 2TB NAS for storing and transferring large files around on my network and don't use it for backup any longer due to its age. Synology, at least for me, just keeps on ticking.</p></div>
	</div>

