			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64715580"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64715580"><p>Disks are binary devices, they have two states, new and full. So go big.<br>So buy at least 4x15TB disks, amd processor, ilo motherboard and Linux + raid5 over the top. I&rsquo;ve run a setup similar to this for 8 years with nfs and bacula for backups or simple tar and scp.<br>The alternative same hardware and truenas.<br>You gain ads, but miss out on flexibility.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64715580">

