	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64716098"><p>I'm a Unix sysadmin and created my 1st NAS at home in 2000 on a used sun system given to me by work.<br>2nd was  dual PII Compaq running Linux with software raid of the drives, LVM for partitioning and ext3 IIRC.</p><p>I have NFS, Samba and a web server.  The OS drives were mirrored.  If I ran out of space on a partition, I could increase the size with LVM &amp; downtime.  Compared to the Netapp I admined at work, it was a pain.</p><p>Downtime is ok on a home system.  The drives failed often enough before TB sized drives wer<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64716098">

